race.comment: LECONFIELD (2) finished fifth two runs back then did well last start but found one better over 1250m at this track, beaten only a nose after being prominent at the turn. Lacey Morrison gets the best out of this four-year-old gelding. Looks well placed so expect another big run. LAZENBY (1) was a determined maiden winner last time out, scoring by a head over 950m here. Has a wide gate to overcome but he cannot be underestimated. OUR IMPACT (3) was well supported last time over 1460m at Home Hill but could only manage third. Strong claims on best figures. LET'S RIDE (11) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a strong race last time out, finishing second and beaten only 1.4 lengths over 1400m at Townsville. Looks well placed so expect a bold display.
